The Living Star Chart

This may be my favorite image.

Celestial navigation traditionally assumes the stars don’t move.

The Pantheon shouldn’t.

The stars themselves evolve.

Every observation updates the map.

Every voyage slightly redraws the heavens.

The navigator is simultaneously:

* sailor
* astronomer
* cartographer
* instrument maker

Every expedition improves navigation for the next one.

