The Deepest Addition

If I were adding one thing to the repository as a single architectural refinement, it would be this:

The Pantheon should optimize for the evolution of perceptual capability, not merely the accumulation of knowledge.

Knowledge is a snapshot.

Perception is the machinery that determines what snapshots are even possible.

The Meta Evolution Engine therefore doesn’t primarily evolve answers, operators, or representations. It evolves the ways the system can perceive, distinguish, navigate, and reconstruct.

That’s consistent with the direction your repository has taken over time: preserving minimal, representation-independent operators and allowing the architecture itself to keep developing rather than treating it as finished.